Regain Control of Your Data Every app your organization uses can increase security risks, complicate compliance, and place additional burdens on already busy IT departments. Unlike other apps, SmartDraw doesn't force you to save files to its own cloud unless that's what you choose. You can keep full control of your data by saving files directly to your existing provider whether that's OneDrive, Google Drive, or something else. Reduce Risk With increasing data breaches and cyber attacks, every new app introduces more data locations and risk. Having your data with a single provider reduces your exposure. SmartDraw lets you save your data where you already save files. You don't have to evaluate or worry about someone else's security measures if your data remains with you. Simplify Compliance You already vetted your existing data storage provider to ensure compliance with key regulatory standards you care about such as GDPR, HIPAA, ISO 27001, and others. By leveraging your existing infrastructure in SmartDraw, your organization inherits these compliance measures, reducing the need to implement and document them independently. Use Your Existing Folders and Permissions Reduce IT overhead by saving files to an existing setup. You can avoid having to create a parallel set of shared folders and permissions. SmartDraw will just work with your existing infrastructure. SmartDraw Has Enterprise-Level Security If you do choose to store your data with SmartDraw, you can be rest assured SmartDraw's storage meets all the regulatory standards you require. Read more about our security policies here. Connecting SmartDraw to Your Existing IT Infrastructure OneDrive You can choose to save diagrams to a connected Microsoft OneDrive account. Once connected, you can even create diagrams directly from OneDrive. See more about SmartDraw's integration with OneDrive. SharePoint You can save diagrams directly to Microsoft SharePoint by connecting your instance. Once connected, your team can make visuals directly from within SharePoint. See more about SmartDraw's integration with SharePoint. Google Drive You can save your SmartDraw files to a connected Google Drive account. Once connected, your team can also create diagrams directly from Google Drive. See more about SmartDraw's integration with Google Drive. Other Storage SmartDraw also works with Dropbox and Box, learn how to connect to those providers here. See more about all of SmartDraw's storage integrations.
